<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1811,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1811,1836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Integument dark-brown. Pubescence light whitish gray. Antennomeres III–XI brown. Each elytron with 
<number box="[297,325,1847,1871]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="10.0">10</number>
brown spots arranged in three transverse rows of three spots each one and a single spot in apical region, the first row just below anterior margin, the second before the middle with a lateral spot not visible dorsally and the third row with a large “m” shaped fascia laterally. Apices of tibiae and tarsomeres dark-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1811,2016]" lastBlockId="2.[153,1436,151,680]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
Upper eye lobes well separated, distance between them twice the width of the upper lobe. Antennae exceeding elytral apices at antennomere VI. Scape 
<number box="[610,620,1992,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[630,645,1992,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="6.0">6</number>
shorter than antennomere III; III–IX subequal in length, 
<date box="[1293,1331,1992,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
X 
<number box="[1321,1331,1992,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
/ 
<number box="[1341,1356,1992,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="6.0">6</number>
longer than IX, antennomere XI twice the length of X. Pronotum finely, uniformly punctate; sides with a basally dilated lateral tubercle. Anterior region of pronotum with a transverse depression (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1106,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[337,1271,761,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[299,1289,733,1873]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Eucharitolus depressus sp. nov. 1, holotype, male; 2, paratype, female; 3, detail of pronotum, 4, detail of protibiae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211116/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[1090,1106,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Prosternal process slightly narrowed in the middle, almost as wide as procoxal cavity. Mesosternal process 
<number box="[1051,1065,223,247]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[1075,1087,223,247]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="3.0">3</number>
as wide as mesocoxal cavity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[153,1436,151,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
Elytra almost 
<number box="[359,394,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="3.5">3.5</number>
times as long as prothorax, surface with fine punctures, becoming denser in anterior half. Humeri slightly projected anteriorly and laterally. Region in the anterior third, near the suture, with a slight depression. Apices obliquely truncate, angles slightly produced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[153,1436,151,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
Protibiae with a small ventral tooth on basal third (
<figureCitation box="[796,869,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[337,1271,761,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[299,1289,733,1873]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Eucharitolus depressus sp. nov. 1, holotype, male; 2, paratype, female; 3, detail of pronotum, 4, detail of protibiae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211116/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[852,869,367,391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); apex of mesotibiae with two acute projections; metatarsomere I 
<number box="[350,385,404,428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as II–III together. Apex of urotergite V strongly emarginate; urosternite V emarginate, “v” shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[153,1436,151,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">Female. Protibial tooth reduced. Apex of urotergite V acute and gradually narrowed distally; urosternite V obliquely truncate and slightly emarginate, exceeding elytral apices by almost half its length.</paragraph>
