<figureCitation box="[288,354,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[337,1271,761,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[299,1289,733,1873]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Eucharitolus depressus sp. nov. 1, holotype, male; 2, paratype, female; 3, detail of pronotum, 4, detail of protibiae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211116/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
Fig. 
<number box="[340,354,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) and the protibiae with a small ventral tooth on the basal third (
<figureCitation box="[1068,1137,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[337,1271,761,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[299,1289,733,1873]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Eucharitolus depressus sp. nov. 1, holotype, male; 2, paratype, female; 3, detail of pronotum, 4, detail of protibiae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211116/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
